WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
I am reading to you today a very mysterious topic,

00:05.000 --> 00:10.000
which is connected with the structure of capital, its price and risks,

00:10.000 --> 00:18.000
which cause changes in the structure of capital in the economic life of any business.

00:18.000 --> 00:20.000
A few words about myself.

00:20.000 --> 00:25.000
I have been engaged in financial work, financial thematics, for many years.

00:25.000 --> 00:30.000
I have been in the business for about 20 years,

00:30.000 --> 00:37.000
starting from the position of the chief accountant of the heavy machinery plant.

00:37.000 --> 00:43.000
For three years I worked as a financial director in two companies

00:43.000 --> 00:50.000
and headed the analytical center of the Moscow Control and Accounting Chamber,

00:50.000 --> 00:55.000
where the structure of capital plays a decisive role,

00:55.000 --> 01:02.000
because the state structures are particularly concerned

01:02.000 --> 01:07.000
about increasing the volume of loans due to budgetary means.

01:07.000 --> 01:12.000
I have divided the structure of this topic into three modules.

01:12.000 --> 01:18.000
In the first module, which is dedicated to the concept of the structure of capital,

01:18.000 --> 01:23.000
I will talk about the problem of optimization or the choice of the rational structure of capital.

01:23.000 --> 01:27.000
We will look at the approaches that have been developed in practice

01:27.000 --> 01:33.000
to feel the line for which the future borrowing destroys this business.

01:39.000 --> 01:43.000
You probably often hear that the whole world lives in debt.

01:43.000 --> 01:45.000
And this is true.

01:45.000 --> 01:52.000
It is the borrowing that allows people to expand their investment opportunities,

01:52.000 --> 02:01.000
to implement ambitious problems that are facing them at the moment, strategic plans.

02:01.000 --> 02:13.000
But the recent debt crisis in the United States still makes people understand

02:13.000 --> 02:17.000
that there are objective borrowing boundaries,

02:17.000 --> 02:25.000
which lead to bad results for both citizens and companies.

02:27.000 --> 02:32.000
Therefore, there is an optimal structure of capital

02:32.000 --> 02:37.000
that allows business to keep going and even develop.

02:37.000 --> 02:47.000
The most important thing is to understand what factors affect the structure of capital.

02:47.000 --> 02:52.000
You will see in textbooks such a definition of the structure of capital,

02:52.000 --> 02:55.000
a combination of debt and personal capital,

02:55.000 --> 02:59.000
which should be balanced by business assets every time.

02:59.000 --> 03:01.000
This is called the structure of capital.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.000
There is a slightly different definition.

03:03.000 --> 03:07.000
It is related to what I have just said.

03:07.000 --> 03:14.000
The structure of capital is a proportion of personal capital and borrowing,

03:14.000 --> 03:18.000
which has developed in a company at the moment.

03:18.000 --> 03:22.000
The differences are not fundamental.

03:22.000 --> 03:27.000
First, in the extensive interpretation of the structure of capital,

03:27.000 --> 03:31.000
I do not talk about how long it takes.

03:31.000 --> 03:36.000
Secondly, I talk only about the long-term debt related to the development of the business.

03:36.000 --> 03:41.000
Let's see why we need to understand the structure of capital in this way.

03:41.000 --> 03:44.000
If we look at the structure of balance,

03:44.000 --> 03:47.000
which you have already seen in previous lessons,

03:47.000 --> 03:50.000
it becomes clear that in both parts of the balance,

03:50.000 --> 03:53.000
capital is represented in a special way.

03:53.000 --> 03:57.000
In the right part of the balance, the passive part,

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
it is represented as the capital function.

04:00.000 --> 04:06.000
In this role, capital gives an idea of the structure of the business.

04:06.000 --> 04:10.000
Who is behind this company?

04:10.000 --> 04:15.000
What are the responsibilities for the company that are threatening?

04:15.000 --> 04:21.000
All the ideas about the sources of financing can be seen in the right part of the balance.

04:21.000 --> 04:24.000
This is the capital function.

04:24.000 --> 04:29.000
But in this form, no one needs capital.

04:29.000 --> 04:32.000
It must give a return.

04:32.000 --> 04:37.000
It starts giving a return when we move to the left side of the balance.

04:37.000 --> 04:41.000
Capital is represented as the capital function.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
The function of making new money.

04:44.000 --> 04:50.000
It is the left side of the balance that gives an idea of the profile of this business,

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
of its financial complex.

04:53.000 --> 04:58.000
Here we often find money.

04:58.000 --> 05:01.000
In the cash or at the account, which I mentioned.

05:01.000 --> 05:05.000
It is clear that this is not working money.

05:05.000 --> 05:08.000
Therefore, it is not capital.

05:08.000 --> 05:14.000
The task of the financiers is to build the structure of capital,

05:14.000 --> 05:17.000
both in the active and passive part,

05:17.000 --> 05:24.000
so that the presence of money will provide you with the current payment ability.

05:24.000 --> 05:27.000
And capital gave the greatest return.

05:27.000 --> 05:35.000
The problem is that in the left part we find the current debt,

05:35.000 --> 05:37.000
which we call the debitory debt.

05:37.000 --> 05:40.000
In the right part, the creditory debt.

05:40.000 --> 05:45.000
Here you can see the connection between the two definitions of the structure of capital.

05:45.000 --> 05:48.000
In normal conditions, the current debt,

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
that is, we credit the business,

05:50.000 --> 05:54.000
the reflection finds this operation in the debitory debt.

05:54.000 --> 05:57.000
We are credited, suppliers and contractors.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
This will be the creditory debt.

05:59.000 --> 06:02.000
And in normal conditions, they are balanced.

06:02.000 --> 06:08.000
If we remove these two components from the left and right parts of the balance,

06:08.000 --> 06:11.000
then we will come to a rigid definition of the structure of capital.

06:11.000 --> 06:15.000
Indeed, the proportions between the own and long-term borrowed sources.

06:15.000 --> 06:17.000
But the difficulty is in what?

06:17.000 --> 06:26.000
If there are not enough financial assets in the company's assets,

06:26.000 --> 06:32.000
then the company will inevitably experience financial ruptures at certain points.

06:32.000 --> 06:39.000
That is, at the right time, there is simply not enough money to carry out some operations.

06:39.000 --> 06:45.000
Or, as people sometimes say, a deficit of capital for development is found.

06:45.000 --> 06:49.000
On the other hand, if there are a lot of money,

06:49.000 --> 06:52.000
the company works with excess liquidity.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
It is not active enough.

06:54.000 --> 07:04.000
Therefore, users of financial reporting, for which the company provides its data,

07:04.000 --> 07:07.000
will immediately react to this.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
Therefore, when you decide to solve the case,

07:11.000 --> 07:21.000
pay close attention to how much money is rationally available in the business situation.

07:21.000 --> 07:29.000
If it is excess liquidity, then the amount of money should be brought to the norm,

07:29.000 --> 07:33.000
released and given simply to shareholders.

07:33.000 --> 07:38.000
This is their income, and you are fulfilling your mission.

07:39.000 --> 07:44.000
Or, if you find that you have a deficit of capital for development,

07:44.000 --> 07:47.000
then you simply cannot touch the cash.

07:47.000 --> 07:53.000
Where do the original requirements for the structure of capital arise?

07:55.000 --> 08:01.000
In any textbook on financial management, you will find that capital has functions.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.000
There are usually three of them.

08:04.000 --> 08:10.000
First, the capital itself should provide an adequate basis for the growth of the business.

08:10.000 --> 08:16.000
The second important function is that the capital should be in such a size

08:16.000 --> 08:23.000
that the possible losses that occur from time to time in any business

08:23.000 --> 08:27.000
can be absorbed and neutralized.

08:27.000 --> 08:34.000
Finally, the capital should be in such a size that in the event of bankruptcy,

08:34.000 --> 08:39.000
which is the pattern of the market economy,

08:39.000 --> 08:48.000
it can protect creditors and shareholders from serious losses.

08:48.000 --> 08:51.000
So, these are the three functions of capital.

08:51.000 --> 08:56.000
If you look closely at them in relation to each particular company,

08:56.000 --> 09:03.000
you will see that the capital structure that the financiers should optimize is predetermined.

09:03.000 --> 09:12.000
The importance of choosing a rational capital structure is determined by a number of conditions.

09:12.000 --> 09:21.000
For example, if a company has a capital structure that provides money to the external environment at a high price,

09:21.000 --> 09:28.000
it immediately enters the limitation of its investment decisions.

09:28.000 --> 09:34.000
The demand for the profitability of the invested capital immediately becomes very high.

09:34.000 --> 09:37.000
The company becomes selective in choosing investments.

09:37.000 --> 09:42.000
That is, the company's investment opportunities immediately decrease.

09:42.000 --> 09:46.000
This is the first very important initial condition.

09:46.000 --> 09:53.000
The second one is that there are often additional limitations on investment opportunities.

09:53.000 --> 09:59.000
The company cannot respond flexibly enough to the challenges of the external environment,

09:59.000 --> 10:06.000
it becomes manoeuvrable in competition, and very often it simply gets out of competition.

10:06.000 --> 10:13.000
The concern for the flexibility of the business is considered the number one concern today.

10:13.000 --> 10:19.000
Finally, if the proportion of the borrowed capital is not optimal,

10:19.000 --> 10:23.000
internal conflicts often arise.

10:23.000 --> 10:27.000
They are often called professional conflicts or agency conflicts.

10:27.000 --> 10:34.000
Between the management, that is, the higher management of the company, and the owners or shareholders.

10:34.000 --> 10:39.000
Between the owners and creditors.

10:40.000 --> 10:48.000
These conflicts greatly reduce the investment opportunities of the business, if they begin.

10:48.000 --> 10:56.000
Therefore, if such a conflict has arisen in the company at the moment,

10:56.000 --> 11:02.000
there is no question of additional capital attractions.

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
It just cannot happen.

11:04.000 --> 11:09.000
We should forget about it before these conflicts disappear.

11:09.000 --> 11:13.000
Otherwise, the value of capital will simply destroy your business.

11:13.000 --> 11:23.000
A very important concept related to the choice of the rational structure of capital is the sufficiency of capital.

11:23.000 --> 11:27.000
Let me tell you about such a case from practice.

11:27.000 --> 11:36.000
It is clear that the problem of the sufficiency of capital arises when we think about the coming financial year.

11:36.000 --> 11:40.000
How much does the company want to earn?

11:40.000 --> 11:52.000
It is clear that in order to increase the income, additional assets are needed.

11:52.000 --> 11:56.000
In order to purchase additional assets, additional money is needed.

11:56.000 --> 12:04.000
And from this, the conflict of these circumstances immediately forms the criteria of the sufficiency of the capital.

12:04.000 --> 12:11.000
How much capital is needed for the coming year to ensure the planned income?

12:11.000 --> 12:13.000
Pay attention to the slide.

12:13.000 --> 12:21.000
The capital itself is equal to the net profit minus the bracket R minus I.

12:21.000 --> 12:28.000
This is a very significant term in finance.

12:28.000 --> 12:36.000
The profitability of assets calculated on net profit or economic profitability is often called.

12:36.000 --> 12:42.000
And this value characterizes the debt rate.

12:42.000 --> 12:46.000
At what price does the firm receive the debt sources?

12:46.000 --> 12:52.000
The difference in this bracket is multiplied by the amount of the long-term debt.

12:52.000 --> 13:11.000
If you look closely at the formula calculator, the load on the capital itself is either net profit or net profit.

13:11.000 --> 13:15.000
But here the problem arises.

13:15.000 --> 13:18.000
The value in the bracket can change the sign.

13:18.000 --> 13:21.000
That is, R minus I can change the sign.

13:21.000 --> 13:28.000
Suddenly, if the value in the bracket is negative, the minus gives a plus.

13:28.000 --> 13:38.000
Thus, the attraction of loans in this situation only aggravates the demand for one's own capital.

13:38.000 --> 13:42.000
The load on net profit increases even more.

13:42.000 --> 13:47.000
How much asset is required to obtain this amount of profit?

13:47.000 --> 13:53.000
To do this, it is enough to divide net profit by economic profitability.

13:53.000 --> 13:59.000
And we will get the amount of additional financing in the form of a long-term debt.

13:59.000 --> 14:04.000
We will see this expression in the bracket more than once.

14:04.000 --> 14:12.000
It is desirable that all listeners remember the economic nature of this expression.

14:12.000 --> 14:16.000
A number of important consequences arise from this formula.

14:16.000 --> 14:28.000
The planned profit is achievable only if the additional payment from these assets increases the profit.

14:28.000 --> 14:35.000
In this case, the increase in assets due to debt is economically justified.

14:35.000 --> 14:40.000
This is where the statement that the whole world lives in debt comes from.

14:40.000 --> 14:43.000
What is the exact amount of asset growth needed?

14:43.000 --> 14:52.000
To do this, we simply need to divide the amount of profit we want to obtain by economic profitability.

14:52.000 --> 15:06.000
Obviously, if R minus I, the need to finance this business in terms of one's own capital, increases enormously,

15:06.000 --> 15:13.000
the load will be solely on net profit.

15:13.000 --> 15:23.000
So, if we look at the economic meaning of the bracket,

15:23.000 --> 15:28.000
multiplied by the amount of long-term debt divided by economic profitability,

15:28.000 --> 15:39.000
the amount of financial resources that companies need to compensate in risky conditions will not be economically justified.

15:39.000 --> 15:42.000
Here is an example from practice.

15:42.000 --> 15:52.000
One of the well-known companies located in Moscow is the shareholder society, the Institute of Hydro Projects.

15:53.000 --> 16:04.000
This is a complex and very strong economic formation represented by three branches in Russia,

16:04.000 --> 16:13.000
located in different places, starting from the Caucasus and ending in Eastern Siberia.

16:13.000 --> 16:18.000
And three branches abroad, the most powerful in India.

16:18.000 --> 16:26.000
You probably heard that Russia won a tender for the construction of the GSTERI in India,

16:26.000 --> 16:32.000
and the Institute was the participant of this tender.

16:32.000 --> 16:38.000
Therefore, the branch abroad was of great importance in the fate of this company.

16:38.000 --> 16:47.000
It would seem that a well-known company with a long economic history, which has been working steadily for many years,

16:47.000 --> 17:01.000
should have its own capital in such a size to insure such a complex structure of its business from various disorders.

17:02.000 --> 17:05.000
But here is what happened.

17:05.000 --> 17:17.000
At one point, a very bad signal came from a subsidiary company located in Eastern Siberia.

17:17.000 --> 17:24.000
The company had great debts to the tax authorities.

17:25.000 --> 17:30.000
The tax authorities soon learned that there was a head office in Moscow,

17:30.000 --> 17:35.000
and all the claims to the subsidiary company were sent to the head office.

17:35.000 --> 17:44.000
And this is where the problem of capital sufficiency arose for the first time in this company.

17:44.000 --> 17:50.000
If all the debts of this subsidiary company were paid by the tax authorities,

17:50.000 --> 17:54.000
the Institute could have been closed.

17:54.000 --> 18:00.000
Why? Because the company never talked about the sufficiency of capital.

18:00.000 --> 18:07.000
But if we consider the function of capital, it should be in such a size

18:07.000 --> 18:12.000
that the company could insure all the economic disorders of its structural subdivisions.

18:12.000 --> 18:17.000
This risk was not included in the established capital of this company.

18:17.000 --> 18:21.000
Therefore, it was necessary to urgently change the structure of capital,

18:21.000 --> 18:30.000
increase the long-term loans, restructure, take up tax debts,

18:30.000 --> 18:35.000
and gradually pay off the debts and leave the company afloat.

18:35.000 --> 18:46.000
What factors affect the choice of the rational structure of capital?

18:46.000 --> 18:52.000
First, the external environment in the conditions of globalization plays a huge role.

18:52.000 --> 18:55.000
The capital markets are connected all over the world today.

18:55.000 --> 19:03.000
If you pay attention, our stock indexes on the main platforms of the IMF and the RTS have sharply fallen.

19:04.000 --> 19:10.000
There were no internal reasons for the fall of the stock prices.

19:10.000 --> 19:17.000
It turned out that the fall of the stock prices in the United States

19:17.000 --> 19:21.000
on the platforms of the major Asian companies

19:21.000 --> 19:26.000
has brought the fall of the stock prices in Russia.

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
So what is behind this?

19:28.000 --> 19:34.000
A number of companies were forced to abandon all decisions on the optimization of the capital structure,

19:34.000 --> 19:39.000
to stop their programs of going to the exchange platforms

19:39.000 --> 19:46.000
in order to attract additional money from the placement of the IPO program,

19:46.000 --> 19:50.000
and to wait for the favorable moment.

19:51.000 --> 19:58.000
If you look at this slide, you will see two groups of factors.

19:58.000 --> 20:06.000
The left side of the slide gives an idea of the factors that form the capital structure.

20:06.000 --> 20:18.000
If they prevail in this business, you put the priority of your own financing of this business.

20:18.000 --> 20:30.000
And vice versa, if the factors that are described in the right side of the slide prevail,

20:30.000 --> 20:33.000
you put the priority of your own financing of this business.

20:33.000 --> 20:39.000
So, the instability of the economic environment.

20:39.000 --> 20:47.000
If this is found, the company puts the priority of its own financing.

20:47.000 --> 21:01.000
And vice versa, if the environment is favorable, the company puts the priority of its own financing.

21:01.000 --> 21:07.000
But here we should keep in mind that the economic environment or the level of stability of the economic environment

21:07.000 --> 21:13.000
pre-determines the so-called investment period in each specific country.

21:14.000 --> 21:17.000
And based on the definition of the capital structure,

21:17.000 --> 21:22.000
we talked about the ratio or the proportion of the own and long-term borrowers,

21:22.000 --> 21:32.000
what is the long-term borrower in the world of this reason of the formation of the capital structure.

21:32.000 --> 21:41.000
Until recently, literally 2-3 years ago, the investment period of Russia did not exceed the frame of 3 years.

21:41.000 --> 21:49.000
Therefore, if you pay attention, the basic characteristics of our bonds were 3-year bonds.

21:49.000 --> 21:59.000
Although the Western world or the companies that place their bonds on developed stock exchanges

21:59.000 --> 22:02.000
immediately claim from 5 and more years.

22:02.000 --> 22:08.000
Here is the difference in the investment climate, in the conditions of the external environment

22:08.000 --> 22:14.000
and the structure of the capital that the company can afford.

22:14.000 --> 22:22.000
A very important value in the structure of the capital is the lifetime of the company.

22:22.000 --> 22:26.000
The company is just starting its own business.

22:26.000 --> 22:29.000
It is clear that no one will give it serious money in debts,

22:29.000 --> 22:33.000
and therefore all hope is on its own source of financing.

22:33.000 --> 22:40.000
If the company has a history, it expands, then of course such a company will be able to finance its debt.

22:40.000 --> 22:44.000
It will be burdened with debts, the turnover expands,

22:44.000 --> 22:49.000
more and more money is required to maintain the business's power,

22:49.000 --> 22:55.000
and hence, of course, the tendency to long-term financing is obvious and justified.

22:55.000 --> 23:05.000
A lot of things in the choice of the structure of the capital are determined by the qualifications of the financial services of this company.

23:05.000 --> 23:15.000
It should be understood that borrowing or attracting debt sources for financing is a very complex financial transaction.

23:15.000 --> 23:21.000
It requires a huge amount of knowledge, requirements for debt financing,

23:21.000 --> 23:26.000
and criteria that determine the rate of debt financing.

23:26.000 --> 23:36.000
If the financiers are not qualified enough, then of course the capital will be very expensive for them,

23:36.000 --> 23:42.000
and most likely they will be burdened with their own sources of financing.

23:42.000 --> 23:48.000
On the contrary, if the company has a very high financial culture,

23:48.000 --> 23:56.000
then it is not difficult to enter the capital market, and the company can easily attract borrowing capital.

23:56.000 --> 24:04.000
An important factor in determining the structure of capital is the level of financial dependence.

24:04.000 --> 24:14.000
What is it? It is the ratio of the own and borrowed funds, which is equal.

24:14.000 --> 24:18.000
But most often, and you will notice it in the books,

24:18.000 --> 24:25.000
it is written that the ratio of 50 to 50, that is, 50 own and 50 borrowed funds,

24:25.000 --> 24:37.000
is the necessary level of financial independence, that is, the equality of own and borrowed funds.

24:37.000 --> 24:51.000
If the company has this ratio, then of course it is limited in the possibilities of further expansion of financial dependence,

24:51.000 --> 24:54.000
and it will be burdened with its own capital.

24:54.000 --> 25:01.000
And vice versa, if the ratio of debt and own capital is far from the 50 to 50 limit,

25:01.000 --> 25:10.000
then of course the company can afford to increase the volume of debt sources and expand its turnover at this expense.

25:10.000 --> 25:14.000
It will be burdened with debt financing.

25:14.000 --> 25:22.000
A very important factor in determining the structure of capital is the limitation of the financial resources.

25:22.000 --> 25:29.000
Either they are limited in the national capital market, or access to them is not limited.

25:29.000 --> 25:41.000
If there are limitations, then our market history of Russia is based on the fact that we have always had a sharp deficit of debt financing sources.

25:41.000 --> 25:47.000
In the conditions of limitation, of course, the company will be burdened with its own financing.

25:47.000 --> 25:54.000
And vice versa, if the access to the capital market is free, the company will be happy to borrow,

25:54.000 --> 25:58.000
and the cost of borrowing will not be catastrophic for it.

25:58.000 --> 26:08.000
You have probably heard a lot of talk in recent years about the fact that the company should be open to the outside world.

26:08.000 --> 26:18.000
That is, references that your information is confidential, close the doors to you on the capital market.

26:18.000 --> 26:22.000
No one will talk to you about borrowing.

26:22.000 --> 26:27.000
And vice versa, in the conditions of transparency of financial information that you give to the outside world,

26:27.000 --> 26:35.000
of course, investors and creditors have the opportunity to assess your risks, your financial needs,

26:35.000 --> 26:40.000
your possible return on investment of financial resources.

26:40.000 --> 26:45.000
And, of course, the access to debt financing of such a company is open.

26:45.000 --> 26:53.000
A very important value in determining the tendency to either debt financing or own financing

26:53.000 --> 26:59.000
determines how you feel about the implementation of investment projects.

27:00.000 --> 27:10.000
If the company is talking about the implementation of projects related to the minimization of costs for the attraction of capital,

27:10.000 --> 27:18.000
that is, the minimum cost is the main condition for the implementation of this investment project.

27:18.000 --> 27:21.000
Often such investments are called mandatory.

27:21.000 --> 27:25.000
Apparently, when you studied this topic, you talked about them.

27:26.000 --> 27:35.000
Of course, companies with such investment projects should rely exclusively on their own sources of financing.

27:35.000 --> 27:46.000
And vice versa, if the investment portfolio of the company is rich, it has several promising investment projects in turn,

27:46.000 --> 27:54.000
and if we are talking about the payable costs for the implementation of the money attracted for these projects,

27:54.000 --> 27:57.000
then here the financial work begins.

27:57.000 --> 28:05.000
Here, the work to find the optimal structure of capital is a very important block of financial activity,

28:05.000 --> 28:09.000
and the company will, of course, be happy to attract debt financing.

28:10.000 --> 28:17.000
Finally, a very important value in choosing the structure of capital is the profile of each particular company.

28:17.000 --> 28:23.000
As they say, if a company is mastering some pioneering projects,

28:23.000 --> 28:32.000
that is, it has innovative ideas that give it competitive advantages,

28:33.000 --> 28:45.000
but you understand that any pioneering project or any innovation is associated with a huge risk of their future success.

28:45.000 --> 28:54.000
It is impossible to calculate in advance all the consequences of the implementation of such an innovation project.

28:54.000 --> 28:57.000
Therefore, in the initial period of implementation of this project,

28:57.000 --> 29:01.000
it is possible to talk exclusively about the sources of financing.

29:01.000 --> 29:13.000
