48:44.000 --> 48:51.000
What approaches have been developed in the world of science and practice in terms of optimizing the structure of capital?

48:51.000 --> 48:56.000
The most popular approach is called the compromise or traditional method.

48:56.000 --> 48:58.000
Pay attention to this slide.

48:58.000 --> 49:06.000
If I look at the coordinates of the price of capital and the financial dependence, i.e. the structure of capital,

49:06.000 --> 49:16.000
I will see how the structure of capital and its value will be formed, depending on what money I attract to the development of the business.

49:16.000 --> 49:20.000
The upper curve characterizes the capital itself.

49:21.000 --> 49:34.000
It is customary to think that since the very development of the business, its expansion, increase in debt dependence, i.e. the increase in debt and capital itself,

49:34.000 --> 49:42.000
the value of the capital has been increasing evenly, while the total value of the capital has been gradually decreasing.

49:42.000 --> 49:56.000
It is clear that the larger the amount of debt sources in the structure of capital, the more you save on the tax rate, and therefore the value of the capital decreases.

49:56.000 --> 50:09.000
But pay attention to the fact that during the development or at a certain stage of the life cycle, you enter a phase when both your own capital and the debt for the company become more expensive.

50:09.000 --> 50:18.000
The first person among the scientists who noticed this situation, in a dispute with the first-time researchers Miller and Modigliani, was Durand.

50:18.000 --> 50:25.000
He observed dozens of large American firms and discovered this thing.

50:25.000 --> 50:39.000
He said that up to a certain point, the value of the capital or the average value of the capital, the average cost of capital, decreases.

50:39.000 --> 50:49.000
And only after some point, the value of the source of financing increases.

50:49.000 --> 50:56.000
This means that there is an optimal structure of capital that must be adhered to.

50:56.000 --> 51:13.000
If an entrepreneur felt this line, saw that the cost of money went up, he must return to the previous situation and accept that this is the optimal structure of capital for him.

51:13.000 --> 51:19.000
This is why this traditional method of optimization is written in every textbook.

51:19.000 --> 51:31.000
This concept is not strictly scientific, because it is impossible to mathematically calculate this point of the fracture when the cost of capital begins to increase.

51:31.000 --> 51:46.000
The uniqueness of each firm, and all firms are unique, does not give a chance to mathematically express the point of the fracture.

51:46.000 --> 51:55.000
In practice, the structure of capital is often optimized by purely operational profits.

51:55.000 --> 52:02.000
What is the point? Of course, the desire for profit is and will be the rational goal of any business.

52:02.000 --> 52:18.000
The theory states that with the increase of borrowed funds in the structure of capital, investors and creditors do not realize the risk of the company increasing.

52:18.000 --> 52:25.000
The firm works, shows good turnover, so it does not cause much concern.

52:25.000 --> 52:38.000
As a result, the cost of borrowed funds remains constant, does not change from time to time, and, of course, raises the total profit of the company.

52:39.000 --> 52:57.000
Because investors do not realize the increasing risk, they are satisfied with the increase in the profit, and they hope for a multiple return on investment of debt sources in the increase of profit.

52:57.000 --> 53:07.000
Their ultimate goal is realized, and they encourage the increase of the use of borrowed funds in this company.

53:07.000 --> 53:13.000
What is the conclusion? Yes, everyone is satisfied.

53:13.000 --> 53:25.000
By using borrowed funds, you can reduce the price of your capital, increase the value of the company for shareholders, but everything is up to time.

53:25.000 --> 53:30.000
There is one very important assumption that should always be taken into account.

53:30.000 --> 53:48.000
We said that at some point in time, the expansion of the financial volume does not cause concern for creditors or shareholders, but the increase in financial dependence still occurs, and therefore the financial risks increase.

53:49.000 --> 54:03.000
In this case, the growth of turnover is ignored, and the business risk is ignored, which is associated with the transformation of the marginal profit into the operational profit.

54:04.000 --> 54:13.000
But in the future we will show that both the financial and business risks act simultaneously, they do not work separately.

54:13.000 --> 54:22.000
This assumption also doubts the optimality of this method, its scientific evidence.

54:22.000 --> 54:30.000
Still, some experience and intuition are present in optimizing the structure of capital in this method.

54:30.000 --> 54:43.000
There is another method recognized by science, I believe it is the most scientific proof.

54:43.000 --> 54:50.000
The method of operational profit. If we are talking about purely operational profit, then we are talking about the overall operational profit.

54:50.000 --> 55:02.000
This method is widely used in practice, because it explains the situation for any company, the probability of bankruptcy.

55:02.000 --> 55:14.000
