01:02:01.000 --> 01:02:04.000
or build, as in the case of the extreme, a financial pyramid.

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:14.000
This is what Radon did. After the check of the Moscow Accounting Chamber, a huge financial pyramid was revealed.

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:19.000
The company worked, nothing threatened at first glance.

01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:33.000
But who was the guarantor in the last instance of payments for this financial pyramid in the event of its collapse?

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:44.000
Of course, the Moscow government. As soon as this became known, a number of restrictions were immediately adopted by the Moscow City Council,

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:58.000
and the guarantors were immediately assigned to the Moscow government, and the budget structure was incorporated.

01:02:58.000 --> 01:03:01.000
A number of restrictions were made.

01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:24.000
Here is how the construction of a certain capital structure affects its value, and the reaction of the owners or managers of this business to the exit from this situation.

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:35.000
Why did Radon's capital price soar?

01:03:35.000 --> 01:03:38.000
It is clear that you have to pay for convenience.

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:41.000
One thing is a one-time loan, and the other is a credit line.

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:50.000
That is, at any time, in the event of a financial collapse, a certain level of access to debt financing is always open.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:52.000
For this convenience, you have to pay.

01:03:52.000 --> 01:04:03.000
Therefore, the cost of the loan in the form of a credit line was at least two times higher than the Central Bank's refinancing rate.

01:04:03.000 --> 01:04:12.000
This is the influence of the capital structure and the form of debt financing on the capital price.

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:22.000
The second factor that takes part in the formation of the capital price policy is the time cost of money.

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:27.000
The time factor is taken into account in the cost of money.

01:04:27.000 --> 01:04:37.000
Today's money is much more expensive than money in a year, two, three, and with the help of discounting, we take into account the time cost of money.

01:04:37.000 --> 01:04:43.000
The next factor that determines the price of capital is the risk level.

01:04:43.000 --> 01:04:46.000
Each company, as we said, is unique.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:53.000
Therefore, the internal structure of business and financial risks is distributed differently.

01:04:53.000 --> 01:05:04.000
And the assessment of capital depends on how much emphasis is placed on one or the other side, namely, on the business or financial risk.

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:06.000
Imagine a simple situation.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:09.000
The business risk of a company is huge.

01:05:09.000 --> 01:05:14.000
Can a company afford a high financial risk related to debt financing?

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:16.000
Of course not.

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:18.000
Therefore, the structure of capital will be predetermined.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:21.000
From here, its cost is determined.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:22.000
And vice versa.

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:30.000
A company with a small business risk can afford a higher financial risk.

01:05:31.000 --> 01:05:38.000
The key role in determining the price of capital is the state of the capital market.

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:43.000
You can often hear that the market is always right.

01:05:43.000 --> 01:05:47.000
In a sense, this is true.

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:55.000
The truth is that the market is represented by a huge number of different participants, creditors, investors.

01:05:56.000 --> 01:06:02.000
They study the situation of companies that ask for financing sources.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:09.000
They say that almost everything is known about this company.

01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:15.000
That is, they minimize a huge amount of information about this company, about its relations with counteragents,

01:06:15.000 --> 01:06:22.000
the logic of behavior with investors, whether they pay dividends or do it irregularly.

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:24.000
The market knows all this.

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:28.000
From here, an average value of capital is formed.

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:36.000
It is a bar that determines the value of capital for each particular company.

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:39.000
How is the task of assessing the price of capital solved?

01:06:39.000 --> 01:06:43.000
It is clear that, based on the structure of capital,

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:50.000
if the task of attracting additional funds for development is set,

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:56.000
the shareholder capital, that is, the structure of power in this company, should not be washed away.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:07:00.000
This task can be solved only with the help of debt financing.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:08.000
The capital market evaluates the need for a company in debt financing

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:14.000
and will determine its level of financial, production or business risk.

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:16.000
This is also a synonym.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:24.000
From here, a certain value of borrowing for a particular company is formed.

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:30.000
Combining the value of one's own capital and debt financing,

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:34.000
one can determine the average cost of capital.

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:39.000
This is the value of capital for a particular company.

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:44.000
How to determine the value of capital for any company?

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:53.000
We know that there are two different sources of capital financing in calculation.

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:56.000
Debt financing, loan, interest, bonds, and so on.

01:07:56.000 --> 01:08:00.000
And the share of participation or shareholding in the company management.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:03.000
Stocks, shares and other forms.

01:08:03.000 --> 01:08:16.000
The combination of these two sources of financing allows us to determine the total value of capital for a particular company.

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:19.000
What do I do in this case?

01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:31.000
Without going into detail about the share of each source of financing in the total structure of capital,

01:08:31.000 --> 01:08:35.000
I determine the value of each source separately.

01:08:35.000 --> 01:08:41.000
I determine the value of the loan, the value of the bond, and so on.

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:44.000
I evaluate the shares separately.

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:50.000
And then, having received two assessments, I look at their mutual influence.

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:53.000
Mutual influence is always there.

01:08:53.000 --> 01:08:59.000
How will the mutual influence of two prices affect the final assessment of the company?

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:07.000
This is a tedious analytical work that must be done every time the sources taken separately are calculated.

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:17.000
When I have done all this, I put the final conclusions in the final formula of average costs

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:22.000
and determine how much capital is spent for the company today.

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:25.000
The value of the sources taken separately.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:31.000
If we take the debt sources as the main priority in modern business,

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:39.000
then we can talk about the value of the bond and the value of the loan financing.

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:44.000
You probably know how to calculate the value of a loan.

01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:51.000
This is the percentage and the corresponding expenses for the loan, divided by the amount of the loan.

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:55.000
In general, this is how it was explained to you.

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:59.000
But there is one important remark.

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:04.000
The loan scheme is well known in the world.

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:09.000
This is the simplest approach to the percentage payments to the amount of the loan.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:12.000
It is not often used in the modern world.

01:10:12.000 --> 01:10:24.000
For example, a banker is giving out a loan and wants to take some risks.

01:10:24.000 --> 01:10:26.000
What can he do?

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:31.000
He can leave the amount of the compensation balance at your account.

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:35.000
Usually, this is no more than 15% of the amount of the main debt.

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:40.000
In this case, the value of the loan is increasing.

01:10:40.000 --> 01:10:44.000
The denominator is not the total amount of the loan,

01:10:44.000 --> 01:10:49.000
but the minus of the compensation balance.

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:53.000
The denominator decreases, the whole expression of the fraction increases,

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:56.000
and the value of the loan increases.

01:10:56.000 --> 01:11:05.000
There are other more severe loans for business and other borrowers.

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:08.000
For example, a loan to a loan office.

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:17.000
Even buying a car on credit today will most likely be done according to this scheme.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:22.000
Why is it considered the most applicable for borrowers?

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:29.000
Because the calculation of the debt, despite the fact that the loan was registered for 3 or 5 years,

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:34.000
the calculation of the debt begins from the very beginning of the registration.

01:11:34.000 --> 01:11:41.000
That is, a month or a quarter has passed, and a part of the main debt will have to be paid off in installments.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:45.000
If you look closely at the general scheme of this debt,

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:51.000
then for a company, with a percentage rate of 15% per year,

01:11:51.000 --> 01:11:54.000
this loan will cost almost 30% per year.

01:11:54.000 --> 01:11:57.000
That is, the rate is almost doubled.

01:11:57.000 --> 01:12:03.000
Because you use less and less loan amount, and the rate remains constant.

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:07.000
These are the features of the assessment of credit resources.

01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:12.000
As for bonds, when assessing bonds as a source of debt financing,

01:12:12.000 --> 01:12:18.000
it should be borne in mind that there is a current profitability and profitability to repayment.

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:24.000
The current profitability is calculated in the same way as the cost of credit resources.

01:12:24.000 --> 01:12:33.000
The investment of the coupon income multiplied by the nominal cost of the bond is divided by its current cost.

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:36.000
What percentage you get, you get.

01:12:36.000 --> 01:12:39.000
This is the current profitability of the bond.

01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:44.000
But for the borrower company, the total profitability is important.

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:46.000
That is, the profitability to repayment.

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:56.000
If I add the amount that I have to pay at the time of repayment of the bond,

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:59.000
and I have to return the nominal,

01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:04.000
then this total cost will give the profitability to repayment.

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:09.000
The general formula looks very simple.

01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:14.000
The amount for a period of, say, N years,

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:22.000
let it be 5 years, which is a fashionable term of bond loans in Russia today.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:29.000
Here is the amount and component consisting of 5 years.

01:13:30.000 --> 01:13:36.000
The coupon income divided by the unit plus the rate of profitability required.

01:13:36.000 --> 01:13:41.000
The denominator is the discount multiplier.

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:48.000
I have specially brought you two tables of discounting in the lecture conspectus,

01:13:48.000 --> 01:13:53.000
so that you can calculate the cost of the debt financing sources yourself.

01:13:54.000 --> 01:13:59.000
The second component of the denominator is the discount rate.

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:04.000
Here, keep in mind that the amount required by the norm of profitability

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:11.000
in economic terms means the lowest profitability limit that suits the investor.

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:18.000
The money owners are ready to give you for investment.

01:14:18.000 --> 01:14:23.000
If we leave the value of R as unknown and solve the equation of R,

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:26.000
we will get the profitability of repayment.

01:14:26.000 --> 01:14:31.000
Today, the built-in functions of Excel allow us to do this very quickly.

01:14:31.000 --> 01:14:38.000
If I want to calculate this parameter immediately,

01:14:38.000 --> 01:14:41.000
then there is a method of approximate calculations.

01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:45.000
The sum of the coupon income,

01:14:45.000 --> 01:14:50.000
plus the denominator minus the current value of the bond,

01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:53.000
divided by the number of years, for example, by 5,

01:14:53.000 --> 01:15:01.000
and the denominator is the half-sum of the denominator and the current profitability of the bond.

01:15:01.000 --> 01:15:03.000
What is the error?

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:09.000
Usually, on the second sign, after the comma, that is, 12.24%,

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:11.000
I had doubts in the fourth.

01:15:11.000 --> 01:15:16.000
So, for approximate calculations, it is suitable, you can use it.

01:15:16.000 --> 01:15:23.000
It is much more difficult to calculate the value of the share.

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:28.000
I believe that at the moment, there is no way in the world of science

01:15:28.000 --> 01:15:33.000
that gives the opportunity to accurately estimate the value of the share.

01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:38.000
Although, several Nobel Prizes have been awarded for this,

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:42.000
there are no accurate calculations for today.

01:15:42.000 --> 01:15:45.000
What is the problem here?

01:15:45.000 --> 01:15:50.000
Any value, including capital, is determined by the future,

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:59.000
by some expectations of how much income I will receive from owning this financial instrument.

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:02.000
But the future is always unpredictable, and that's the whole problem.

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:07.000
The problem of the valuation of the share is the problem of taking into account the risk factor.

01:16:07.000 --> 01:16:14.000
The most popular formula for calculating the value of the share is the Gordon formula.

01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:19.000
It is very simple, you just need to understand its economic meaning.

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:23.000
The numerator is D1, that is, the dividend of the first year.

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:26.000
C0 is the base year, the zero year.

01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:28.000
D1 is the first year.

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:33.000
The denominator is the required income rate, R, minus the dividend rate.

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:36.000
What is the value of this formula?

01:16:36.000 --> 01:16:44.000
For young companies, if the formula includes the dividend rate,

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:46.000
that is, the company is developing,

01:16:46.000 --> 01:16:53.000
then this formula can accurately determine the value of the share of such a company.

01:16:53.000 --> 01:16:59.000
For a traditional company, especially for one that pays dividends unevenly,

01:16:59.000 --> 01:17:03.000
the calculation of this formula is very difficult.

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:06.000
What is the weakness of this formula?

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:10.000
It is very difficult to predict the rate of dividend growth.

01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:22.000
Of course, we still rely on our forecasts, on the preceding financial data about this company.

01:17:22.000 --> 01:17:31.000
And yet, it is impossible to take into account the exact repetition of the situation in the future.

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:35.000
The future will always be different from the previous period.

01:17:35.000 --> 01:17:40.000
And taking into account this discrepancy, this is the main problem for financiers.

01:17:40.000 --> 01:17:45.000
In the West, Sharpe model has received a very wide spread.

01:17:45.000 --> 01:17:50.000
Pay attention, the main comparison with ARM is often said.

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:55.000
This is the Sharpe model, the Nobel Prize in Economics.

01:17:56.000 --> 01:18:07.000
The profitability of my share of the company is equal to R0.

01:18:07.000 --> 01:18:12.000
If I move R to the right, it is a risk-free rate.

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:19.000
Plus the expression in the right part of the data,

01:18:19.000 --> 01:18:27.000
Btg multiplied by Mm, this is the profitability of the market portfolio, minus the risk-free rate.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:30.000
This is called the risk-free bonus.

01:18:31.000 --> 01:18:40.000
Each share of a particular company is made up of two components.

01:18:40.000 --> 01:18:43.000
The risk-free rate plus the risk-free bonus.

01:18:43.000 --> 01:18:48.000
The main difficulty of using this formula is the determination of the beta coefficient.

01:18:48.000 --> 01:18:56.000
It expresses the reaction of a particular share of the company to the change in the market price.

01:18:56.000 --> 01:19:05.000
Let's say you trade your shares in the RTS system, the Russian fund platform.

01:19:05.000 --> 01:19:14.000
The value of the market portfolio, that is, the total shares that are presented there, is 16%.

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:19.000
Last week, the RTS index went down.

01:19:19.000 --> 01:19:23.000
It dropped to 4% immediately.

01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:30.000
Look at how the value of your share of the company reacted to the change in the external environment.

01:19:30.000 --> 01:19:33.000
It dropped to 8%.

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:37.000
Its reaction is more acute than the reaction of the entire market.

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:41.000
This means that the beta coefficient is greater than 1.

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:46.000
If we take such proportions, it is close to 2.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:54.000
The reaction is more severe to the change of the external environment than the reaction of the market.

01:19:54.000 --> 01:20:01.000
This coefficient in Western practice, where a huge statistical array of data is accumulated,

01:20:01.000 --> 01:20:07.000
exists an agency that constantly provides data for a huge number of companies.

01:20:07.000 --> 01:20:15.000
In Russian practice, obtaining this data is difficult, and therefore it is quite difficult to use this formula.

01:20:15.000 --> 01:20:19.000
The simplest way is to use the income approaches.

01:20:19.000 --> 01:20:22.000
The second is to take into account the risk factor.
